        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does a 401(k) reduce taxable income?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes. Traditional 401(k) contributions are made pre-tax and directly reduce your taxable income for the year. If you contribute $23,500, your taxable income is reduced by that amount. Roth 401(k) contributions are made after-tax and do not reduce current taxable income, but qualified withdrawals in retirement are tax-free."
        }
      }]
